    Colinet-Caplan Syndrome: History of an Outbreak of Autoimmune Disease in Scouring Powder Workers.
After silica in scouring powders was replaced with less hazardous materials later in the 20th century, no further cases have been reported. Although scouring powder disease is a historical phenomenon, autoimmune disorders linked to occupational exposure to silica and coal dust have not disappeared but instead are reemerging among those who work with silica-based artificial stone and in other dusty trades.
